🎥: @Detroitlionsnfl

node.text: @tombrady finally breaks down how that trophy toss really happened, with his eyewear partner @christophercloos.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 17, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing football and grass.

node.text: Detroit Lions announced they have released long snapper Don Muhlbach, who played 17 seasons and 260 games for the team, the second-most in team history behind only Jason Hanson. “Don Muhlbach will go down as one of the all-time Detroit Lions greats,” said Lions’ owner Shelia Ford Hamp. His release came on his 40th birthday.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 17, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text: 49ers cut Josh Rosen today. Since Arizona drafted him in the first round in 2018, Rosen has played for four NFL teams - the Cardinals, Dolphins, Buccaneers and 49ers. 49ers waived Rosen in order to claim CB Davontae Harris off waivers from the Baltimore Ravens.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people playing football and outdoors.

node.text:
Early diagnosis is that Steelers WR Chase Claypool suffered a “minor ankle sprain” today and “should be fine”, per source.

📸 Matt Freed

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adam Schefter on August 17, 2021 tagging @presidentmal, @seahawks, and @unisportsmgmt. May be an image of 1 person, playing football, ball and text that says 'SEAHAWKS BREAKING NEWS'.

node.text: Jamal Adams’ agents, Kevin Conner and Robert Brown of @unisportsmgmt, confirmed that their client and the Seahawks have reached agreement on a four-year contract extension with a maximum value of $72 million, including a $20 million signing bonus. Adams becomes the highest-paid safety in NFL history.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 17, 2021. May be an image of football.

node.text: Trade: Panthers sending offensive tackle Greg Little to the Dolphins in exchange for a 2022 seventh-round pick.

node.text: Jaguars have released TE Tim Tebow.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 16, 2021. May be an image of football.

node.text: Falcons say their team is 100% fully vaccinated. The club is believed to be the first NFL team to reach the milestone. The Falcons did have five players on the COVID-19 reserve list at the start of training camp, but all have since been removed from the list.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing football and text that says 'BOSE'.

node.text: Bucs’ HC Bruce Arians said that he does not expect Tom Brady to play Saturday in Tampa’s second preseason game against the Titans. And he won’t be alone. “We probably won’t play any starters,” Arians said.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 16, 2021. May be an image of football.

node.text: Dolphins’ WR Allen Hurns has a wrist injury that will require surgery and he is expected to miss three months, per source.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and playing football.

node.text: Bengals’ QB Joe Burrow won't play in the second week of the preseason vs. Washington, per Cincinnati HC Zac Taylor. Bengals continue to be careful with Burrow, the former No. 1 overall pick who tore his ACL last season.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: ESPN has signed three-time Pro-Bowl QB Alex Smith to be an analyst. Smith will appear on multiple shows and in various roles, mainly surrounding NFL programming, including SportsCenter, Monday Night Countdown on select weeks and Sunday NFL Countdown from time-to-time.
